The paper deals with video understanding and natural language processing, which are both subfields of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed framework also employs deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Additionally, the paper introduces a novel structure to combine sentence fragments, which can be considered a contribution to machine learning (cs.LG) research.
